Package: tritonIngest
Title: Tabular Data Ingestion Toolkit
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R:
    person("Travis", "Shepherd", email = "travis.shepherd@tritonenv.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Domain-agnostic primitives for ingesting messy field and laboratory
    data workbooks: all-as-text reading of CSV/TSV/XLSX with content-based type
    sniffing, worksheet enumeration including hidden sheets, long/wide/transposed
    layout detection and reshaping, declarative column contracts with synonym and
    opt-in fuzzy auto-mapping, reusable JSON column-mapping profiles, censored
    (non-detect and over-range) value parsing and substitution, unit
    reconciliation, and row-level validation checks. Shared by the
    water-chemistry-qaqc and bw-analysis-code projects so each can reuse the same
    ingestion plumbing without duplicating it. Contains no domain knowledge,
    statistics, or plotting.
